{
  "_notes": [
    "Fill the world_points with measured coordinates in one shared room coordinate system.",
    "Recommended convention: x and y on the floor plane, z upward, one room corner at [0, 0, 0].",
    "Use room corners and both bottom/top column corners so the points span the full volume.",
    "Click the image_points on the original distorted images. Do not undistort first if you pass distortion coefficients below.",
    "If you do not know the distortion yet, leave it as zeros and solve pose first. Then replace with checkerboard/Charuco-calibrated distortion later and rerun.",
    "The 24mm lens value only gives an initial focal-length guess. It does not determine distortion coefficients by itself.",
    "known_xy is now used by a second-pass optimizer that keeps the camera center x/y fixed and refines only rotation plus z.",
    "focal_search can optionally loosen fx/fy together for a specific camera while keeping cx/cy and distortion fixed.",
    "If your footage already has in-camera lens correction baked in, keeping distortion at zeros is reasonable as a first pass.",
    "The image_points below are full-resolution 3840x2160 coordinates, rounded to integers and converted from bottom-left input into top-left image coordinates.",
    "Per-camera reference stills are raw_data/results_cropped/c1-ref.png through c4-ref.png, and frame_glob points at raw_data/results_cropped/<camera>/**/rgb_full/*.png so transforms_room.json enumerates the full-resolution RGB frames.",
    "The room_top_* z values still need to match the real visible top-corner height in your room coordinate system. Leaving them at 1.0 will distort the recovered camera z scale."
  ],
